com.ibm.team.build.ant.task
Class StartBuildTask

java.lang.Object
  Task
      com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.AbstractTeamBuildTask
          com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.StartBuildTask

public final class StartBuildTask
extends AbstractTeamBuildTask

Ant task to start a team build. It can be used to start a build for either an existing or new build request. All properties in the build definition are automatically defined in ant after executing this task.

Required attributes are:

  • resultUUIDProperty - The ant property to store uuid of the build result for the started build.

Optional attributes are:

  • requestUUID - The ant property used to indicate the build should be started using an existing request.
  • buildDefinitionId - The build definition id, such as 'Integration' to start a build for. Can not be specified if requestUUID is used otherwise it's required.
  • engineId - The id of the engine that is performing the build. Can not be specified if requestUUID is used otherwise it's required.
  • label - The label for the build result.
  • resultUUIDFile - The path relative to the base directory of the build file or the full path to a file in which to store the uuid of the build result created as part of the start build task. The file is formatted as a java.util.Properties format and contains a property with the name specified by resultUUIDProperty.
  • autoComplete - Indicates if the build that is started should be automatically completed. This is true by default. When it is true ant must be launch with the -listener parameter and refer to the TeamBuildListener class.
See AbstractTeamBuildTask for additional required and optional attributes.

Since:
0.5
